<br>
On numerous occasions (one recently) we've gone up to Hate after another guild has left.  The Revenants are usually still up, as are the spite golems that line the wall near Maestro.  The banshees and kirakueis on the back side of Maestro's hall are also left up.  I think out of the last 10 post raid visits I've been on, only once has the entire first floor been clear.<br>
<br>
Also, due to the separation, two raids can coexist safely so long as both raid parties have experience pullers and scouts.<br>
<br>
<br>
Fear, on the other hand, is not really sharable until after the break-in and the south roamers are cleared.  And for most guilds the break-in is the worst part.  To have another guild wander in right after a break would be disappointing since the first party faced extreme risk breaking in.<br>
<br>
<br>
Of course, it really depends on the type of raid (amateur, novice, experienced).<br>
